      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "ELEVATED-CAMERA SCALE (the one manual step)\n\nA bird's-eye plate has no ground plane the\ndepth fit can trust, so single-image scale\nfalls back to a 1.6m eye height -> the whole\nscene goes miniature and the Y=0 grid lands\nmid-scene. The projection is angular and is\nNOT affected — only metric scale.\n\ncamera_height_m = your real altitude:\ncount floors x ~3.2m (45 = ~14th floor).\nEvery downstream metric follows. Set 0 to\ndisable once a shot solves scale on its own."
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
